The new cookware is non-toxic, non-stick  cookware and made free of any harmful chemicals like PFAS. Click the link to shop the new collection. Use code BAKERSROYALE15 to get 15% off. @risacookware #risapartner #risacookware

Speedy Weeknight Skillet Lasagna
Serves 4 -6
1 tablespoon olive oil
1/2 lb. ground beef
1/2 lb. ground sausage
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 t. oregano
1/2 t. red pepper flakes
4 cups of marinara sauce
1 cup chicken stock, more as needed
2 cups shredded fresh mozzarella
1 cup parmesan cheese
chopped parsley
torn basil

Heat 1 tablespoon oil in Risa cookware over medium high. Add beef and sausage and break it up into small pieces. Cook and stir meat mixture just until it starts to brown. Stir in the garlic, oregano and red pepper flakes, cook and stir for another 2 minutes. 

Add the marinara and chicken broth, bring to a simmer. Add the broken pieces of the lasagna to the pan, stir to combine. Spread the to an even layer, making sure to submerge as many of the noodles as possible. 

Reduce the heat to medium. Let simmer uncovered stirring occasionally, making sure to keep noodles below the sauce.  Cook until noodles are al dente, about 20-25 minutes. If the noodles absorb most of the sauce before being cooking through, add  1/4 cup of broth as needed to cook the noodles. 

Once the noodles are cooked, remove pan from the heat. Top with mozzarella and parmesan. Cover and let sit until cheese melts, about 3-5 minutes. Alternately, transfer pan under the broiler to brown the cheese. 

Top with chopped parsley and basil leaves.

#onepanmeal #lasagna #cheesepull #weeknightdinner #easyrecipes

Meet your new favorite dinner hack! #ad Crispy Air Fryer Pierogy Nuggets. It starts with everyone’s favorite — #MrsTsPierogies Classic Cheddar variety. 
 
@MrsTsPierogies makes it easy to level up my everyday meals. This is how we do nuggets when we want a more meatless option, and using the air fryer method makes it easy and fast! And if you are a dipper, I got you covered with homemade options: Sweet and Spicy BBQ, Black Pepper Ranch and Honey Ranch. Here’s to less time in the kitchen and more time at the table with tasty bites like this! 
 
1 16oz Mrs.T’s Classic Cheddar Pierogies
Yields 12 Pierogies
Coating
1 cup flour
2 large eggs, well beaten with 1 tablespoon of water
3 cups ( 8.5oz) potato chips, crushed
 
Create an assembly line for the coating. Place the flour in a shallow bowl. In a second bowl, whisk together the eggs and water. Place the crushed potato chips in a third bowl. 
 
Dredge the pierogy one at a time through the flour, the eggs, and the potato chip mixture, pressing gently to ensure the coating adheres. 
 
Heat the air fryer (or oven) to 400F. Lightly mist an air fryer basket with olive oil. Place each piece on the basket 1/4 inch apart. Air fry (or bake) for 4 minutes. Flip and air fry for another 5 minutes. Cool slightly and enjoy with one or all of the below dips!
 
Honey Mustard
Whisk together one tablespoon of honey, Dijon, and mayonnaise in a small bowl. 
 
Black Pepper Ranch 
Whisk together 4 tablespoons of mayonnaise and sour cream; 1 teaspoon black pepper, onion, and garlic powder; and ½ teaspoon dried parsley, dill, and kosher salt. 
 
Sweet and Spicy Sriracha BBQ
Whisk together 3 tablespoons honey, 2 tablespoons Sriracha and sugar, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, ½ teaspoon smoked paprika and kosher salt.
